article.headline: Navy 76, Lehigh 75
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Matt Fannin scored 16 points and Taj Mathews had 15 as Navy held off a late Lehigh comeback and prevailed 76-75 on Saturday. Corey Johnson had 13 points, George O'Garro scored 11 and David Hooper added 10 for Navy (8-17, 4-8 Patriot League). Jose Olivero scored 23 points for Lehigh (13-12, 7-5), while Joe Knight had 13 points and 10 assists and Jason Mgebroff added 12 points. Navy Lehigh shot just 29 percent from the field in the opening half but Olivero's 13 points helped the Mountain Hawks trail by only one at the half, 32-31. Lehigh tied the score at 43 and took a 47-45 lead on a jumper by James Anderson with 12:29 left, but Navy held the Mountain Hawks without a field goal for the next 5½ minutes and the Midshipmen led by 10, 71-61, with 3:39 to play. Lehigh then went on a 14-5 run, with five points each from Olivero and Knight and four from Mgebroff, to pull within one at 74-73. But Fannin hit a layup with 31 seconds left and Mgebroff's layup with 16 seconds on the clock left the Mountain Hawks one point short.
